body.description: When using the USB C device of Android system, please first determine whether the OTG function of the device is turned on. Please turn it on to use the USB C normally. Warm Tips about USB C Flash Drive: The USB C Flash Drive is Compatible with Tablets or Smartphones with USB Type-C Port and Support OTG Function. The Computer and USB Flash Drive have Different Capacity Calculation Algorithms.The Computer 1G=1024M, USB Flash Drive 1G=1000M.so the USB Flash Drive's Capacity Displayed on the Computer is about 90% of the Actual Identification. Generally the Default System of USB Flash Drive is exfat Format. This format can Transmit the Largest Single File Larger than 4G. The Thumb Drive is made of metal material,due to the fast transmission speed,so It is normal that it has a slight heat during use. please rest assured it does not affect your normal use. High Transfer Speed： -USB 3.0 - Read up to 60 MB/s, Write up to 30 MB/s -Phone port - Read up to 30 MB/s, Write up to 10 MB/s Media Formats Supported： Music: M4A / AIFF / CAF / MP3 / WAV Image: GIF / JPG / PNG / JPEG Video: AVI / FLV / M4V / MKV / MOV / MP4 / RMVB Document: DOC / PPT / XLS / XLSX / PDF / HTML / TXFor copying important data, it is better to complete the double backup first, and then delete the original data, so as to ensure that the data is not lost.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Flash Drive For The Android A23 And Mac Book Pro
reviews.reviewText: I have been looking for a flash drive to connect to my Android cellphone. And the search did reveal some good candidates. But you needed an adapter to connect the drive to the phone.That is until I came across this flash drive.Note to iPhone users. This flash drive does not connect to iPhones.Note to Android users. The OTG (On The Go) must be engaged to connect the drive to your Android phone.Most likely, it is already on by default.The drive has USB and USB-C compatibility.Step one! Verification that the drive would connect to my A23 Android without an adapter.It did, and it did it well.I attached the flash drive to the phone while in sleep mode.The phone woke up and showed a USB device attached to it.Next came the test of the drive to transfer data.The transfer of 60.2 MB of photos from the drive to the phone went down perfectly.After un-mounting the drive from the phone, I transferred the same data to my computer.The data transfer was completed in a few seconds.One Mississippi, Two Mississippi, DoneProsI like the rotation function to go from one connector to the other.There is something called the Stuck Point design. It prevents the random rotation of the drive.The Android phone connector has a cap to protect it.The USB connector does not have a cap. Rotating it into the housing protects it.I like the keyring feature.So far, I have not found any problems with this flash drive. And I recommend it to Android and Mac users.I also recommend verifying that it will work with your device using an online search.My method is to copy/paste the title into the browser and ask, Does this (name of the product) work with (name of device)?This method usually works, but not always.
